** Nonstop Metropolis: An Atlas of Maps Reclaiming New York=E2=80=99s Unto=
ld Stories and Unseen Populations (https://www.brainpickings.org/2016/10/1=
9/nonstop-metropolis-atlas-new-york-rebecca-solnit/?mc_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc=
_eid=3D[UNIQID])
------------------------------------------------------------

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0520285956/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Df47=
6b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

=E2=80=9CA poem compresses much in a small space and adds music=2C thus he=
ightening its meaning. The city is like poetry.=E2=80=9D So wrote E.B. Whi=
te in his timeless 1949 love letter to New York (https://www.brainpickings=
=2Eorg/2014/07/09/e-b-white-here-is-new-york/?mc_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[=
UNIQID]) . But meaning never exists in the singular in this city of infin=
ite multiplicity=2C this mecca of idealism=2C iconoclasm=2C and codified i=
diosyncrasy=2C which means many different things to its eight million inha=
bitants and seven billion onlookers =E2=80=94 a densely populated capital=
 of loneliness (https://www.brainpickings.org/2016/07/11/the-lonely-city-o=
livia-laing/?mc_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C a canine kingdom=
 (https://www.brainpickings.org/2012/11/07/the-big-new-yorker-book-of-dogs=
/?mc_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C an ever-changing castle (htt=
ps://www.brainpickings.org/2012/11/12/changing-new-york-berenice-abbott/?m=
c_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C a city that makes and breaks th=
e American dream (https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/10/06/zadie-smith-fin=
d-your-beach/?mc_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C a city that impe=
lled Walt Whitman to demand
(https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/07/01/walt-whitman-give-me-the-splendi=
d-silent-sun/?mc_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) : =E2=80=9CKeep your=
 splendid silent sun=E2=80=A6 Keep the blossoming buckwheat fields where t=
he Ninth-month bees hum=E2=80=A6 give me the streets of Manhattan!=E2=80=
=9D

The poetics of that multiplicity is what Rebecca Solnit=2C in collaboratio=
n with Joshua Jelly-Shapiro=2C explores in Nonstop Metropolis: A New York=
 City Atlas (http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0520285948/braipick-20=
?mc_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) (public library (http://www.world=
cat.org/title/nonstop-metropolis-a-new-york-city-atlas/oclc/945719047&refe=
rer=3Dbrief_results?mc_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) ) =E2=80=94 th=
e culmination of Solnit=E2=80=99s cartographically scrumptious trilogy=2C=
 after Infinite City: A San Francisco Atlas (http://www.amazon.com/exec/ob=
idos/ASIN/0520262506/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) a=
nd Unfathomable City: A New Orleans Atlas (http://www.amazon.com/exec/obid=
os/ASIN/0520274040/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C=
 exploring =E2=80=9Cwhat maps can do to describe the ingredients and syste=
ms that make up a city and what stories remain to be told after we think w=
e know where we are.=E2=80=9D The trilogy=2C Solnit notes=2C arose from=
 =E2=80=9Cthe belief that any significant place is in some sense infinite=
=2C because its stories are inexhaustible and the few that are well known=
 overshadow the many
worth knowing.=E2=80=9D Any place can therefore be mapped in innumerable w=
ays=2C each casting before the viewer a particular point of view and thus=
 contributing to cartography=E2=80=99s long history as power and propagand=
a. (https://www.brainpickings.org/2012/04/17/magnificent-maps-cartography-=
as-power-propaganda-and-art/?mc_cid=3Df476b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID])

The twenty-six maps=2C each accompanied by an original essay=2C explore fa=
cets of the city as varied as its songscape=2C its linguistic wilderness=
=2C its notable women=2C its brownstones and basketball courts=2C its riot=
s=2C and its various human and physical energy systems.

Cartography: Molly Roy; artwork: Kelsey Garrity-Riley

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0520285948/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Df47=
6b8e46c&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0520285948/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Df47=
